= Latent Diffusion Modeled Based Video Streaming on Semantic Communications 

We presented a novel Semantic Communication (SemCom) framework for real-time adaptive-bitrate video streaming by integrating Latent Diffusion Models (LDMs) within the FFmpeg techniques.

The following are a few problems that we are interested to address:

- Senmatic Error through Noisy Wireless Channel
- Adapted Bitrate Streaming 
- High Bandwidth and Storage Comsumption on Content Delivery Network (CDN)

